iv]:border-border-400 [&amp;_.ignore-pre-bg&gt;div]:bg-transparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Perfect. Let's map out the full plan before touching any code.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Here's what we're building — PawPal+ AI Advisor:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Your existing PawPal+ stays intact as the backbone. On top of it, you're adding:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>A Claude-powered AI chat layer</strong> — user asks natural language questions about their pets, Claude responds with care advice using the pet/task data already in the system</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>A guardrail system</strong> — validates AI inputs and outputs (blocks harmful/nonsensical queries, flags low-quality responses)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>A confidence scorer</strong> — AI rates how sure it is about each response</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>An evaluation/test harness</strong> — a script that runs predefined test cases and prints pass/fail results</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The story you tell for AI security:</strong> <em>"I didn't just build an AI feature — I built a system that audits, validates, and tests AI behavior. That's the security mindset."</em></p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Before we start Step 0 (setting up the new repo), I need to ask — do you currently have your original PawPal+ repo cloned locally on your computer and open in VS Code?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
