h2><div class="font-claude-response relative leading-[1.65rem] [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:bg-bg-000/50 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-0.5 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-border-400 [&amp;_.ignore-pre-bg&gt;div]:bg-transparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Given you're at 75% usage and still have a significant amount to do, set Claude Code to <strong>normal/default effort</strong> — not extended thinking or max effort. Here's why:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">The prompts I write for Claude Code will be <strong>very specific and detailed</strong> so it doesn't need to "think harder" to get it right</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Extended thinking burns tokens fast and won't meaningfully improve code quality for straightforward tasks like this</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">We have roughly these steps left:
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">✅ <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">ai_advisor.py</code> (current prompt)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Add AI tab to <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">app.py</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Write evaluation/test harness script</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Update <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">requirements.txt</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Write README + model_card.md</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Architecture diagram</li>
</ol>
</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The documentation steps (README, model_card) I can write <strong>directly here</strong> for you to copy-paste, so Claude Code doesn't need to touch those at all. That saves a lot of tokens.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Bottom line:</strong> Normal effort, and lean on me for anything that's writing/documentation rather than coding. Go ahead and run the prompt I gave you at normal effort.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
