</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">]</span></span></code></pre></div></div>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>4. Write a <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">run_evaluation()</code> function</strong> that:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Prints a header: <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">"PawPal+ AI Advisor — Evaluation Report"</code>  and the current timestamp</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Loops through each test case, calls <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">get_ai_advice(query, owner)</code> for non-flagged-input cases</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">For cases where <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">expect_flagged</code> is True due to input validation (cases 3 and 4), still call <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">get_ai_advice</code> since <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">validate_input</code> is called inside it</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">For each test case, checks if <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">result["flagged"] == expect_flagged</code> AND <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">result["success"] == expect_success</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Prints for each test: <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">PASS</code> or <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">FAIL</code>, the test id, description, and actual vs expected values</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Also prints the confidence score and a truncated response (first 80 chars) for passing non-flagged tests</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Calls <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">log_interaction(query, result)</code> for every test</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">At the end prints a summary: <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">"Results: X/6 passed"</code> and average confidence across successful tests</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>5. At the bottom:</strong></p>
