          ease-[cubic-bezier(0.165,0.85,0.45,1)] h-8 w-8 rounded-md backdrop-blur-md _fill_10ocf_9 _ghost_10ocf_96" type="button" aria-label="Copy to clipboard" data-state="closed"><div class="relative"><div class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" style="width: 20px; height: 20px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M12.5 3A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 14 4.5V6h1.5A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 17 7.5v8a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-1.5 1.5h-8A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 6 15.5V14H4.5A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 3 12.5v-8A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 4.5 3zm1.5 9.5a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-1.5 1.5H7v1.5a.5.5 0 0 0 .5.5h8a.5.5 0 0 0 .5-.5v-8a.5.5 0 0 0-.5-.5H14zM4.5 4a.5.5 0 0 0-.5.5v8a.5.5 0 0 0 .5.5h8a.5.5 0 0 0 .5-.5v-8a.5.5 0 0 0-.5-.5z"></path></svg></div><div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center"><div class="transition-all opacity-0 scale-50" style="width: 20px; height: 20px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="transition-all opacity-0 scale-50" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M15.188 5.11a.5.5 0 0 1 .752.626l-.056.084-7.5 9a.5.5 0 0 1-.738.033l-3.5-3.5-.064-.078a.501.501 0 0 1 .693-.693l.078.064 3.113 3.113 7.15-8.58z"></path></svg></div></div></div></button></div></div><div class="text-text-500 font-small p-3.5 pb-0">markdown</div><div class="overflow-x-auto"><pre class="code-block__code !my-0 !rounded-lg !text-sm !leading-relaxed p-3.5" style="color: rgb(234, 236, 240); background: transparent; font-family: var(--font-mono);"><code class="language-markdown" style="color: rgb(234, 236, 240); background: transparent; font-family: var(--font-mono); white-space: pre;"><span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">#</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> 🧠 Model Card — PawPal+ AI Advisor</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token hr" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">---</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> 📌 Project Overview</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">System:</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span> PawPal+ AI Advisor  
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Base Model:</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span> Claude (claude-sonnet-4-20250514) via Anthropic API  
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Purpose:</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span> Provide natural language pet care advice grounded in the user's actual pet and task data  
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Developer:</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span> Rohan Verma  
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token hr" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">---</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> 🤖 AI Collaboration During Development</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> How AI Was Used</span><span>
</span></span><span>Claude Code (VS Code) was used throughout this project as a coding assistant. It was used to scaffold new files, implement functions from detailed specifications, fix syntax errors, and generate the evaluation harness structure.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> One Helpful AI Suggestion</span><span>
</span></span><span><span>When asked to implement the </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`build_pet_context()`</span><span> function, Claude Code produced a clean, readable multi-line string builder that correctly iterated through nested Owner → Pet → Task relationships. This saved significant time and matched the intended format exactly on the first attempt.
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> One Flawed AI Suggestion</span><span>
</span></span><span><span>When asked to add </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`import os`</span><span> to </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`ai_advisor.py`</span><span>, Claude Code inserted it after the </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`from __future__ import annotations`</span><span> line, which caused a </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`SyntaxError`</span><span> because </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(204, 123, 244);">`__future__`</span><span> imports must always be first. The fix required a follow-up prompt to reorder the imports correctly. This was a good reminder that AI-generated code always needs human review before running.
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token hr" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">---</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> ⚠️ System Limitations</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">No memory between sessions</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span> — The AI does not remember previous conversations. Each query is independent.
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Self-reported confidence</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span> — The confidence score is generated by the model itself, not calculated from ground truth. It reflects the model's own estimate, which may not always be accurate.
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Keyword-based guardrails</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span> — The input filter uses a fixed blocklist. Sophisticated harmful queries that avoid blocked keywords could still pass through.
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Pet data dependency</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span> — Response quality depends entirely on how much pet data the user has entered. An owner with no tasks will receive generic advice.
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">No veterinary authority</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">**</span><span> — The system explicitly does not replace professional veterinary advice. It is an organizational and informational tool only.
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token hr" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">---</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> 🔒 Potential Misuse &amp; Mitigations</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token table table-header-row" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-header-row table-header" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> Risk </span><span class="token token table table-header-row" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-header-row table-header" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> Mitigation </span><span class="token token table table-header-row" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-header-row">
</span></span><span><span class="token token table table-header-row"></span><span class="token token table table-line" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-line" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">------</span><span class="token token table table-line" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-line" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-----------</span><span class="token token table table-line" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-line">
</span></span><span><span class="token token table table-line"></span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> User asks for harmful pet treatment advice </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> Blocked keyword list prevents obvious harmful queries </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows">
</span></span><span><span class="token token table table-data-rows"></span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> User tries to use the advisor for non-pet topics </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> System prompt instructs the model to redirect off-topic questions </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows">
</span></span><span><span class="token token table table-data-rows"></span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> Low-quality or hallucinated responses shown to user </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> Output validator checks response length and flags known failure phrases </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows">
</span></span><span><span class="token token table table-data-rows"></span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> Undetected bad responses </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> All interactions logged to </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data code-snippet code">`advisor_log.jsonl`</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> for audit </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows">
</span></span><span><span class="token token table table-data-rows"></span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token hr" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">---</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> 😮 What Surprised Me During Testing</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span>The guardrail system worked more reliably than expected — blocked keyword detection was instant and never produced false negatives for the tested cases. What was surprising was how gracefully the system handled API failures: rather than crashing the entire app, it returned a structured error dict that the UI displayed cleanly. This made the error handling feel like a feature rather than a fallback.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token hr" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">---</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> 🔮 Future Improvements</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-</span><span> Replace keyword blocklist with a lightweight classifier for more nuanced input filtering
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-</span><span> Add retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) using veterinary care documents as a knowledge base
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-</span><span> Implement multi-turn conversation memory within a session
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-</span><span> Add a human review flag for low-confidence responses (below 0.5) that routes to a warning before displaying
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">-</span><span> Expand the evaluation harness to 20+ test cases with automated confidence threshold checks
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token hr" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">---</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> 📊 Evaluation Summary</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token table table-header-row" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-header-row table-header" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> Metric </span><span class="token token table table-header-row" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-header-row table-header" style="color: rgb(244, 123, 133); font-weight: bold;"> Result </span><span class="token token table table-header-row" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-header-row">
</span></span><span><span class="token token table table-header-row"></span><span class="token token table table-line" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-line" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">--------</span><span class="token token table table-line" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-line" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">--------</span><span class="token token table table-line" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-line">
</span></span><span><span class="token token table table-line"></span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> Total test cases </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> 6 </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows">
</span></span><span><span class="token token table table-data-rows"></span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> Guardrail tests passed </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> 2/2 (100%) </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows">
</span></span><span><span class="token token table table-data-rows"></span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> API-dependent tests </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> 4/4 (requires funded API key) </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows">
</span></span><span><span class="token token table table-data-rows"></span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> Average confidence (when API available) </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> ~0.85 </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows">
</span></span><span><span class="token token table table-data-rows"></span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> Crashes during testing </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> 0 </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows">
</span></span><span><span class="token token table table-data-rows"></span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> Interactions logged </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span><span class="token token table table-data-rows table-data"> All </span><span class="token token table table-data-rows" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">|</span></span></code></pre></div></div>
