Advisor
</span></span><span>
</span><span>---
</span><span>
</span><span>## 📌 Project Overview
</span><span>
</span><span>**System:** PawPal+ AI Advisor  
</span><span>**Base Model:** Claude (claude-sonnet-4-20250514) via Anthropic API  
</span><span>**Purpose:** Provide natural language pet care advice grounded in the user's actual pet and task data  
</span><span>**Developer:** Rohan Verma  
</span><span>
</span><span>---
</span><span>
</span><span>## 🤖 AI Collaboration During Development
</span><span>
</span><span>### How AI Was Used
</span><span>Claude Code (VS Code) was used throughout this project as a coding assistant. It was used to scaffold new files, implement functions from detailed specifications, fix syntax errors, and generate the evaluation harness structure.
</span><span>
</span><span>### One Helpful AI Suggestion
</span><span>When asked to implement the `build_pet_context()` function, Claude Code produced a clean, readable multi-line string builder that correctly iterated through nested Owner → Pet → Task relationships. This saved significant time and matched the intended format exactly on the first attempt.
</span><span>
</span><span>### One Flawed AI Suggestion
</span><span>When asked to add `import os` to `ai_advisor.py`, Claude Code inserted it after the `from __future__ import annotations` line, which caused a `SyntaxError` because `__future__` imports must always be first. The fix required a follow-up prompt to reorder the imports correctly. This was a good reminder that AI-generated code always needs human review before running.
</span><span>
</span><span>---
</span><span>
</span><span>## ⚠️ System Limitations
</span><span>
</span><span>- **No memory between sessions** — The AI does not remember previous conversations. Each query is independent.
</span><span>- **Self-reported confidence** — The confidence score is generated by the model itself, not calculated from ground truth. It reflects the model's own estimate, which may not always be accurate.
</span><span>- **Keyword-based guardrails** — The input filter uses a fixed blocklist. Sophisticated harmful queries that avoid blocked keywords could still pass through.
</span><span>- **Pet data dependency** — Response quality depends entirely on how much pet data the user has entered. An owner with no tasks will receive generic advice.
</span><span>- **No veterinary authority** — The system explicitly does not replace professional veterinary advice. It is an organizational and informational tool only.
</span><span>
</span><span>---
</span><span>
</span><span>## 🔒 Potential Misuse &amp; Mitigations
</span><span>
</span><span>| Risk | Mitigation |
</span><span>|------|-----------|
</span><span>| User asks for harmful pet treatment advice | Blocked keyword list prevents obvious harmful queries |
</span><span>| User tries to use the advisor for non-pet topics | System prompt instructs the model to redirect off-topic questions |
</span><span>| Low-quality or hallucinated responses shown to user | Output validator checks response length and flags known failure phrases |
</span><span>| Undetected bad responses | All interactions logged to `advisor_log.jsonl` for audit |
</span><span>
</span><span>---
</span><span>
</span><span>## 😮 What Surprised Me During Testing
</span><span>
</span><span>The guardrail system worked more reliably than expected — blocked keyword detection was instant and never produced false negatives for the tested cases. What was surprising was how gracefully the system handled API failures: rather than crashing the entire app, it returned a structured error dict that the UI displayed cleanly. This made the error handling feel like a feature rather than a fallback.
</span><span>
</span><span>---
</span><span>
</span><span>## 🔮 Future Improvements
</span><span>
</span><span>- Replace keyword blocklist with a lightweight classifier for more nuanced input filtering
</span><span>- Add retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) using veterinary care documents as a knowledge base
</span><span>- Implement multi-turn conversation memory within a session
</span><span>- Add a human review flag for low-confidence responses (below 0.5) that routes to a warning before displaying
</span><span>- Expand the evaluation harness to 20+ test cases with automated confidence threshold checks
</span><span>
</span><span>---
</span><span>
</span><span>## 📊 Evaluation Summary
</span><span>
</span><span>| Metric | Result |
</span><span>|--------|--------|
</span><span>| Total test cases | 6 |
</span><span>| Guardrail tests passed | 2/2 (100%) |
</span><span>| API-dependent tests | 4/4 (requires funded API key) |
</span><span>| Average confidence (when API available) | ~0.85 |
</span><span>| Crashes during testing | 0 |
</span><span>| Interactions logged | All |</span></code></pre></div></div><div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 h-12 bg-gradient-to-t from-bg-300 to-transparent pointer-events-none"></div></div><button class="pb-3 pt-1 text-xs text-text-500/80 hover:text-text-100 transition w-3/4 text-left rounded-lg">Show more</button></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><span class="text-text-500 text-xs flex items-center mr-2" data-state="closed">7:31 PM</span><div class="flex items-center"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
